articles.author: Ayelet Sheffey, Juliana Kaplan
articles.title: What will happen to Social Security, SNAP in a government shutdown - Business Insider
articles.description: A federal government shutdown will happen Saturday if Congress doesn't agree on funding by then. It could risk benefits Americans rely on.
articles.content:
There's a government shutdown looming
, and it could mean even more economic woes for Americans.
Come September 30, the government will run out of funding
  unless Congress steps in with a stopgap… [+4153 chars]
